  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The archetypal Eldritch Knight⁠⁠ combines the martial mastery common⁠ to all fighters with a careful study of magic. Eldritch Knights use magical Techniques similar to those practiced by wizards. They focus their study on two of the eight schools of magic: Abjuration and Evocation. Abjuration⁠ spells⁠ grant an Eldritch Knigh⁠t⁠ additional Protection in battle, and evocation⁠ spells⁠ deal damage to many foes at once, extending the fighter’s reach in combat⁠. These knights learn a comparatively small number of spells⁠, committing them to memory instead of keeping them in a Spellbook.</p>\n<h3>Eldritch Knight Features</h3>\n<p>3rd Level: @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.GQkUiE7dqIvo2clh]{Spellcasting}, @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.eCZkP7lGRryyoaNJ]{Weapon Bond}</p>\n<p>7th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.2UgbNDxMq4Zzr8lJ]{War Magic}</p>\n<p>10th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.oLqO3qBAkdCcav6t]{Eldritch Strike}</p>\n<p>15th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.2tqBnd8Nu9x0mfjU]{Arcane Charge}</p>\n<p>18th Level: @Compendium[5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.nE2A6QHFzUAIHe57]{Improved War Magic}</p>",
